&quot;Alright. Well, We can start with my hut. It's a very smiple place. Afterwards, I'll show you the Tanais River, the Symbol of my Valley.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yakut walked away from the fireside holding Tanna's hand kinda taking her with her. She walked up to her hut which was next to Raven's and across from Lynn's. She nodded to the Gaurds to let her and Christanna pass. Yakut entered her hut. The Queen's Hut was decorated with shaman robes hanging from the wall near the door, a shelf stocked with herbs and other shaman nessecities. Yakut had a nice sized bed in the center of her room with a big blanket made from animal skins. There was a desk in the corner where Yakut did all her writing and tribal scrolls. The desk was a gift from Gabrielle (XAmznGabrielleX) who had inspired Yakut to keep a journal and write like she had on her various journeys with Xena. A small table next to Yakut's bed where some candles where burning. In the back of the hut was a fireplace. Oh and lets not forget Yakut's small praying altar to the Ancients. It had small rug layed out infront of it where Yakut would go into her shamanic trances.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well? What do you think of my humble home?&quot;  <p>§-:¦:-§ Yakut §-:¦:-§

